[2026-03-18T17:32:18.062Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Extract ExecutionPreparer � Separate Enrichment from Dispatch\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: maintenance\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (6/3)\n- **Scan Type**: zen_architect\n- **Generated**: 3/17/2026, 10:29:16 PM\n\n## Description\ndispatchToWorker() in dispatcher.ts does four distinct things: fetch Claude token, load persona from DB, decrypt credentials and assemble env vars, then send the assignment. The credential decryption loop (lines 317-350) and inference profile resolution (lines 357-404) are pure data transformation that does not belong in the dispatch path. Extract a standalone ExecutionPreparer class with a single prepare(request) => ExecAssign method, leaving dispatchToWorker responsible only for token acquisition and sending.\n\n## Reasoning\nMixing enrichment logic with dispatch routing makes both harder to test and reason about. dispatchToWorker currently calls db.getPersona TWICE for the same execution (lines 311 and 412). Extraction eliminates that duplication and makes each concern independently testable � a critical property when credentials and tokens are involved.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\n- **compact-ui-design**: Use `.claude/skills/compact-ui-design.md` for high-quality UI design references and patterns\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation 